modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve HTML element IDs and an initial table state, along with a user-defined action function. Works with a table type and optional string identifiers for interactive elements. Used to configure and trigger dynamic table manipulations through web interface buttons.

Provides functions to parse, generate, and manipulate HTML table structures, including row and column operations, cell value extraction, and table formatting. Works with nested lists and HTML string representations of tables. Used to convert tabular data from web sources into structured OCaml data for further processing.

Initializes and manages a dynamic table structure, allowing addition, removal, and retrieval of rows and columns. It returns the current content as a nested list and dimensions as a pair of integers. Used to manipulate tabular data in real-time during web page interactions.
